cs.CV, cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with face recognition using image processing techniques. The use of entropy measures and kernel entropy component analysis also suggests that it could belong to the information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The mention of real-time implementation suggests that it could also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the use of feature extraction techniques and image databases suggests that it could belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
